'''文岑茨·洪德豪森'''（{{lang-de|Vincenz Hundhausen}}，{{bd|1878年|12月15日|1955年|}}），[[漢名|汉名]]'''洪濤生'''，德国翻译家，著名[[漢學|漢學]]學者。

==生平==
生于[[格雷文布羅赫|格雷文布羅赫]]<ref name=Biegp67>Bieg, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=E2fQI6NDKwQC&pg=PA67&dq=Vincenz+Hundhausen+%22Grevenbroich%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=wS-gUsWlM9GQyQHf44Ao&ved=0CCwQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Vincenz%20Hundhausen%20%22Grevenbroich%22&f=false 67] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=E2fQI6NDKwQC&pg=PA67&dq=Vincenz+Hundhausen+%22Grevenbroich%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=wS-gUsWlM9GQyQHf44Ao&ved=0CCwQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Vincenz%20Hundhausen%20%22Grevenbroich%22&f=false |date=20140104152420 }}. "Who then was Vincenz Hundhausen? Born on the 15th December 1878 in Grevenbroich, approximately 30 km north-west of Cologne,[...]"</ref>，曾任[[北京大学|北京大学]][[德文|德文]][[教授|教授]]，中文向德文翻译者。<ref name=Walravensp92>{{cite book|author=Walravens, p.|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=0F6U82kZXjsC&pg=PA92&dq=%22to+profit+from+the+reputation+of+the+former+newspaper%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=5riQULLwL4LC9gTUoYHABg&ved=0CDIQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22to%20profit%20from%20the%20reputation%20of%20the%20former%20newspaper%22&f=false 92|title=Newspapers in International Librarianship|language=|accessdate=2013-12-05|date=|archive-date=2014-01-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104144000/http://books.google.com/books?id=0F6U82kZXjsC&pg=PA92&dq=%22to+profit+from+the+reputation+of+the+former+newspaper%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=5riQULLwL4LC9gTUoYHABg&ved=0CDIQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22to%20profit%20from%20the%20reputation%20of%20the%20former%20newspaper%22&f=false|dead-url=no}} "xi 洪濤生" (footnote)</ref>

洪濤生翻译了許多[[中国戏剧|中国戏剧]]劇本。<ref name=Walravensp92/> 包括《[[西廂記|西廂記]]》、《[[琵琶記|琵琶記]]》、《[[牡丹亭|牡丹亭]]》的德文版。<ref name=LiuWuChip291>{{cite book|author=Liu, Wu-Chi, p.|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=MUqrApIdoWAC&pg=PA291&lpg=PA291&dq=A.+P.+L.+Bazin&source=bl&ots=oGnS8IAoJq&sig=1o3Z6Vi-oquYr3N4gv-lT61qVYE&hl=en&sa=X&ei=7BOgUoiJOIbmyQH844DQDg&ved=0CCgQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=A.%20P.%20L.%20Bazin&f=false 291|title=An Introduction to Chinese Literature|accessdate=2013-12-05|archive-date=2014-06-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140611235918/http://books.google.com/books?id=MUqrApIdoWAC&pg=PA291&lpg=PA291&dq=A.+P.+L.+Bazin&source=bl&ots=oGnS8IAoJq&sig=1o3Z6Vi-oquYr3N4gv-lT61qVYE&hl=en&sa=X&ei=7BOgUoiJOIbmyQH844DQDg&ved=0CCgQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=A.%20P.%20L.%20Bazin&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Biegp69>Bieg, p. [http://books.google.com/books?id=E2fQI6NDKwQC&pg=PA69&dq=%22Hundhausen+to+translate+more+than+one+hundred+and+twenty+Chinese+texts%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=HDygUvTlCuOayAGqs4HIBA&ved=0CD8Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22Hundhausen%20to%20translate%20more%20than%20one%20hundred%20and%20twenty%20Chinese%20texts%22&f=false 69] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=E2fQI6NDKwQC&pg=PA69&dq=%22Hundhausen+to+translate+more+than+one+hundred+and+twenty+Chinese+texts%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=HDygUvTlCuOayAGqs4HIBA&ved=0CD8Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22Hundhausen%20to%20translate%20more%20than%20one%20hundred%20and%20twenty%20Chinese%20texts%22&f=false |date=20140611100806 }}.</ref><ref name=Merkerp242>Merker, p. 242.</ref><!--The first is for Pipaji, the second for Mudanting, third for Xixiangji-->

